<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_structure_mim  Rule: coordinated_assembly_and_shape 
   <express_ref linkend="product_structure:mim:Product_structure_mim.coordinated_assembly_and_shape"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_structure_mim.coordinated_assembly_and_shape">
The <b>coordinated_assembly_and_shape</b> rule specifies that for a component and an assembly, related by a <express_ref linkend="product_structure_schema:ir_express:product_structure_schema.next_assembly_usage_occurrence"/>, if their respective shapes have been specified and related with an instance of 
<express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation_relationship"/>
, this <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation_relationship"/>
 shall be related with the <express_ref linkend="product_structure_schema:ir_express:product_structure_schema.next_assembly_usage_occurrence"/> with an instance <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.context_dependent_shape_representation"/>. 
<note>This rule intends to constrain the assembly relationship and the placement information to be related, in order to identify for which occurrence of a component a particular position has been specified. </note>
<p>This rule calls the function 
<express_ref
linkend="product_structure:mim:Product_structure_mim.assembly_shape_is_defined"/>
which returns true if the assembly relationship and shape relationship are explicitly related. 
</p>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Product_structure_mim.coordinated_assembly_and_shape.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of <express_ref
linkend="product_structure_schema:ir_express:product_structure_schema.next_assembly_usage_occurrence"/>
for which the 
<express_ref
linkend="product_structure:mim:Product_structure_mim.assembly_shape_is_defined"/>
function returns the value FALSE.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_structure_mim  Function: assembly_shape_is_defined 
   <express_ref linkend="product_structure:mim:Product_structure_mim.assembly_shape_is_defined"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_structure_mim.assembly_shape_is_defined">
The <b>assembly_shape_is_defined</b> is a function that accepts a <express_ref linkend="product_structure_schema:ir_express:product_structure_schema.next_assembly_usage_occurrence"/> as input and returns a boolean result. 
<p>The function returns TRUE if all the following conditions are met:</p>
<ul>
<li>the shape is defined for the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> which is the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.related_product_definition"/>

 and the shape is defined for the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> which is the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.relating_product_definition"/> in the <express_ref linkend="product_structure_schema:ir_express:product_structure_schema.next_assembly_usage_occurrence"/>; 
</li>
<li>the two shapes are related through a <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation_relationship"/>;
</li>
<li>the two relationships are related through a <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.context_dependent_shape_representation"/>.</li> 
</ul>
<p>The function also returns TRUE if the shape of the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.related_product_definition"/>

 or of the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.relating_product_definition"/> is not defined. 
</p> 
<p>The function returns FALSE when the following conditions are met:</p>
<ul>
<li>the shapes are defined for the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.related_product_definition"/>

 and the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.relating_product_definition"/>;
</li>
<li>the shapes are related through a <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation_relationship"/>;
</li>
<li>the <express_ref linkend="product_structure_schema:ir_express:product_structure_schema.next_assembly_usage_occurrence"/> and the <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation_relationship"/>
 are not explicitly related through any <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.context_dependent_shape_representation"/>. 
</li>
</ul>
<note>The definition of this function is identical to its definition in ISO 10303-203:1994.</note>
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Product_structure_mim.assembly_shape_is_defined.assy">
the <express_ref linkend="product_structure_schema:ir_express:product_structure_schema.next_assembly_usage_occurrence"/> that is considered.
</ext_description>
